> <OLD>
>
> Tucson follows the scent of lubricant and tries to quicken his pace.
> Something was bleeding and definitely in need of his help.  He looks on the
> ground, trees,  foliage, and grass to see if a trail is left to follow.  And
> then the electrical smell of something being shorted out, reaches his scent
> receptors and he's quick to follow the scent.
>
> " Whoever you are, stay put, I'm conning to help you!"

<NEW>

As Tuscon bursts through the foliage and brush to 'rescue' the
vicitim, he can see the fallen form of something! As he approached he
could see that it was a sweep, the last bit of lubricant leaking from
a rather large gash in its chest plating. There does not seem to be
any life left in the sweep. If it was what was making the noises from
before it is no longer doing it now, there are no life signatures
comming from it.

All around TUSCON the sounds of the forest have gone silent.

(TAG)

- Preston
